eoconv NEWS -- history of user-visible changes

Copyright (C) 2004-2013 Tristan Miller.  See the end of this file for
copying conditions.

Please send eoconv bug reports to Tristan Miller
<psychonaut@nothingisreal.com>.


Version 1.4

* Rereleased under the GNU General Public License v3.0
* Various minor changes to the internal code and documentation

Version 1.3.1

* Corrected some typos in the documentation

Version 1.3

* Added support for postfix-H, postfix-X, and LaTeX notation
* utf-7, utf-8, utf-16, and utf-32 are now aliases for utf7, etc.
* Many encodings now have aliases with varying capitalization
* Corrected the version number in the --version output
* Expanded documentation for the ISO-8859-3 encoding
* Added `See also' section to documentation

Version 1.2

* Fixed a minor bug hindering batch handling of files from any textual
  encoding to Unicode
* Corrected a misprint in the NEWS file

Version 1.1

* Fixed a minor bug where the --version option did not work

Version 1.0

* Fixed bug in postfix-h notation where `u'-breve was incorrectly
  transliterated to `uh'
* Significantly expanded and revised documentation
* Expanded and revised installation instructions
* Added warning for postfix-h notation
* Added --quiet option to suppress warnings

Version 0.90

* Initial release

